caption: Would love to have given this place a good review on my first visit, however they got my order completely wrong in fact literally the opposite of what I ordered. For reference I ordered a beef and lamb Gyro with extra vegetables and extra to Zieke sauce, when I arrived home I saw that my gyro had no vegetables nor the sauce.
Very good!
Love Greek Spot
24 dollars for two hamburgers.  Not that good.
Very good Greek food!  Gyros are excellent as well as the Greek spot hummus.  We will be back.
Excellent !
I had the Falafel pita. Not the best I had so far. I would pass it.

Went for take out last night and my wife and I were not disappointed. Only a few folks eating outside but the place was buzzing inside with orders waiting to be picked up and the phone ringing off the hook. Our traditional gyro's were outstanding and stuffed with very flavorful lamb. I give this family a lot of respect for opening when they did. As a small deli owner in the NE Cape, I can certainly empathize with opening during a pandemic as we opened at the start of the Great Recession in February 2008. We will be going back.

I will say that even though I was grabbing lunch to go, this was a very pleasant and personable experience.  A refreshing reminder of a time when businesses believed in good food and cared about their patrons.  I can eat a darn good sized meal and I'll tell ya,  I couldn't get all the way around this meal and it was delicious! I will be returning here again and again

It was real authentic Greek food. I tried to eat the whole salad, which is served in a metal bowl... so cute... with some meat on the side fresh off the spitfire...  I felt great afterwards. That’s when you know the ingredients are fresh!!  If I could give them 6 stars I would.  Went back for seconds...Gluten free wrap was spectacular!!!
Had dinner with my future wife here on our first unofficial date, it was awkward and fantastic.  P.S. The Greek Fries made me gassy 💨

THE MOST MEAT I EVER HAD IN A GYRO. The family running the cashier was really friendly and funny. Ordered online and the food was ready right at the time it was requested. The Greek fries were better than the regular fries, only compliant is wish the fries had more seasoning on them but that is a personal preference. Would go here again and again.
Yum yum yummy!!! Great little place
This is FOOD!!! The Greek Spot has the best gyros anyone in my family has ever had! The prices are low for the quality and quantity. Definitely recommend if you're in the Cape Coral area.
Amazing food, great atmosphere and kind people. The portions are huge! Be ready to pack up left overs for home.
real deal

I came all the way from Estero to check this place out and I was not disappointed!  The food was delicious and the owner was very gracious.  It's great to see small businesses thriving in the Cape...I will be back!
A true treasure for Southwest Florida. Delightful service and delicious gyros! Village or Greek salads are a meal in themselves!
Great spot! Nice owners!
Big portions. Great food. Go.
Nice service
Seems like a great place to eat with great reviews. The restaurant was very clean and in order. Going to give them another honest try.
Wow!  Food is great, large portions and friendly service!  Had the Gyro with fries and loving it!!
Just like my mother's recipe
The most delicious food and amazing customer service. Paul, the owner truly makes you feel welcome and at home. I think everyone should eat at this tasty Greek restaurant.

I'm a Chef from New York... Queens New York to be exact... Which has a huge Greek community, with many good restaurants... The Greek Spot is my new favorite place to eat and take out.. I've been once a week since I found them... Don't ask questions just GO
Best gyro I've ever had. Loaded with meat, well seasoned and reasonably priced. Fast, friendly service and they treat you better than family.
We're very happy that this restaurant came to the Cape! Our meal was nothing short of amazing! We tried the pork gyro and the original gyro. Both were expertly crafted. You need to try this place!!!

Those of you who gave this place 4 or 5 stars go to Nomikis Palaka right across the bridge. Worth the $2 toll. Here's why: To go order $48. - my hot food sat there for 20 minutes before someone realized it and blamed it on "waiting for the salad". Nothing like cold take out. - no salad dressing dry salad. Thanks - gyro meat terribly salty - hummus is tastless - young man handling register and expediting orders nice but clueless and hurting the operation.  Brutally bad experience won't be back.
The best gyro I've had anywhere. Friendly atmosphere. Loved it
Food was Great and at a good price.
Delicious Gyros ! Huge and comes with french fries ! Very friendly service , plenty of parking ! If your hungry must go !

I went today to get a village salad and talk about tasty it was Excellent ! I had the gyro meat added tasty as well!! I recommend this place 100% My Greek roots came out today... Home style small but great... Victoria Angeles Kostakis..
Authentic flavors, great service, we will be back often.
I love this place. Great food great service.
Food was awesome!
Great food, the best gyro's.
Food was excellent and friendly helpful staff
The food is phenomenal! Delicious, generous portions and affordable. New fan!
Great food

Amazing! I had the Greek Spot Gyro. Very generous amount of meat, seasoned perfectly, and the Greek spot was on point! The Greek spot fries were so good, don’t forget to try the sauce! Oh.....and the Baklava delicious🥰 Ok, so maybe I tried all the desserts! It’s ALL great! I say you should try one of everything. Thanks Paul and the crew for the great food and friendly service. See you soon!
Excellent food and service!
First time here was so goooddd ☺️ This is the only place I get my gyros now, it’s fantastic! And the fries are delicious. 10/10 would recommend.

I ordered the Greek Spot Gyro it came with fries. It had great flavor. It was hard to get a parking spot at 6:30 - 7 pm on a Friday night. Waiting for a parking spot, I ordered on line by unknowingly sent me to chownow.com. Chownow states without hidden commissions or fees - so not sure if the restaurant or chownow provided higher and fluctuating prices depending on time - for pick up. For example, at 6:30 pm the spanakopita was $8 and it is $6 to walk up and order. I paid  Gryo was 10.25 and walk up is $8.75. At 7:30 pm the spanakopita was $7 and gyro $9.25. This was for online order to pickup (not delivery).

This place is fantastic. My wife and I enjoy the falafel in all forms. The falafel gyro and the falafel on the Greek salad are the favorites. My kids like the chicken pita and of course the cheesesteaks. If, strike that, when you stop by, be sure to ask for a side of the Greek Spot Sauce; it’s delicious. I thought the baklava cheesecake was my favorite dessert until I tried the cookies. They’re soft and crumbly with a perfect gingerbread-like flavor. The family that runs the place is super nice and treats everyone like old friends. Great place to support local!
Cause im black?
Excellent place for Greek food. Good Gyros
Delicious food and friendly service! I’ve brought my husband and mom and they both really liked the food. Would recommend trying out the Greek Spot
Paul and his family are amazing

The food here is wonderful. My stepmother is greek and we used to travel to Athens each year to visit family during the summer months. The fries are about the closest thing to what i used to eat from Athens itself. Can you please sell some of the Lacta bars or some more of the "treats"? We miss these things <3
Delicious!

I like the food at Greek Spot.  A friend & I went there for lunch today.  The owner was taking orders at the cash register & was not wearing a mask.  His wife's mask was down at her chin.  This made me & my friend very uncomfortable.  It doesn't matter if the food is wonderful, if I'm uncomfortable, I won't be returning.

Went for the 1st time yesterday and The Greek Spot did not disappoint. Having teenage boys we all know they are never satisfied. Not this time around they had traditional gyros and when I tell you they didn't know which way to attack it.
Delicious and authentic gyro and falafel.  Excellent service  too.  Planning another visit very soon.
Great food, great people, great vegan options! Falafel, Tzatziki, feta, fries and salad all vegan if that's your thing. Delish!  Owners Paul and Tina are amazing! Friendly and super accommodating.
Gyros were absolutely delicious!

Outstanding!!!! Huge portions of absolutely delicious food.  Traditional gyro and falafel this time around....meat was tender and flavorful. Tzatziki was just perfect......definitely going to try their entire menu!

Fantastic experience from beginning to end. Placed an order online. They tried to contact me multiple times to let me know they were out of an item, but I wasn’t able to receive the calls. When I called to let them know I was there, they immediately let me know and graciously made a substitution for us right then. And added a bonus baklava! The food was absolutely delicious. We had the traditional gyro, pork gyro, and a kids lemon chicken meal. All the meat was perfect, sauces amazing and those Greek fries!!! Great service, great food - we’ll be back and spreading the word.

we are so happy that greek food is back in cape coral i had pork gyros and my wife falafel. both was great. the owner family is super friendly-we felt like being in greece where we always spend our summers. so we know that this food is authentic. not the stuff you get on a greek fest or so. i mean the stuff what you are told it is greek but it is not ;-) we will be back soon
Amazing food, fast and friendly service. A great experience at a local family-owned spot!!
Amazing Gyros! I love this place. The owner is super friendly and the atmosphere pleasant.  I can grab to go or eat there and am always satisfied.
Excellent! great addition to cape coral. Get here before everyone finds out.
Awesome Gyro, yes the lamb is shaved off the spool. Fairly priced. Wish i had more stars to give

My husband had come here with his friend and loved it so he took me there today. This is a great place for Gyros. That’s what we had and I give my recommendation as excellent. We will come back and try more on the menu. My husband wanted to just get it to go but I said let’s eat out front on the tables. So we did, lovely Greek music piped in and along with lunch it felt like we were on vacation. Try it you’ll like it
Excellent Gyros! Nice family business. Dog friendly.

Absolutely delicious and authentic Greek cuisine! We had the olive and cheese platter, gyro platter, hummus with warm pita bread, cheeseburger with french fries, and the Greek Salad. Don't forget the baklava. It's so yummy! The owner, Tina and family are very friendly and welcoming. We'll definitely be back often.

Really great Greek food done by some great, friendly people.  Gyros are delicious and stuffed with meat.  Burgers are great and the salads are loaded up with fresh ingredients.  The owners and the family staff are always welcoming and genuinely good people!!

Supporting the locals!! Today is our day off so we finally had a chance to visit this special spot that we have heard so many great things about- THE GREEK SPOT! ❤️👍😃 Amazing food! Amazing people! Family operated business,that opened on October 5th of this year!!!! 👍👍👍 We had a privilege to meet the owners Tina and Paul and their children Niko and Gloriana and  super fun and friendly grandmother Irene who was wearing a T-shirt with a slogan “ Today will be amazing “  😃🙏  The best Greek Food Ever! So fresh and delicious ! If you have not been here yet it is a must! Highly recommend !!! 👍❤️😃👍😋😋😋😋

The food is amazing! Definitely would recommend coming here. The hummus with the feta is to die for. I went a few weeks ago for the first time and ordered it for take out and someone who worked there let me know it takes longer to get your food if you order take out because the customers who sit down usually get their food first. So if you are more in a rush order it for there and take it with you!
Great Place and awesome services. tasty food and drinks friendly staff great place.
Hit the Greek Spot again on Friday night it was money!  The family takes it over the top.  Nothing but great food and love at this joint.

"Enjoy a Gyro with wine, a Greek salad with beer, or scrumptious baklava with an Orangina for dessert"  "Get ready for a true experience of the Mediteranean here in SWFL"  Greek Version: ACTIVATE YOUR GREEK! "Απολαύστε ένα γυροσκόπιο με κρασί, μια ελληνική σαλάτα με μπύρα, ή νόστιμο μπακλαβά με ένα Orangina για επιδόρπιο"  "Ετοιμαστείτε για μια πραγματική εμπειρία της Μεσογείου εδώ στο SWFL"

Paul and family are the new Greek Kings of the Cape! We had the greek salad with falafel which was fresh and full of flavor. Top notch customer service and incredible quality for the price. Even in the middle of a VERY busy Saturday evening rush, they took time to welcome me in and make sure my experience was well worth the 25 minute drive.
Best Greek food I have ever had and I don’t usually like Greek food so it is a big thing that I LOVE IT!!!!!
Thank you.
Service is typically good. It has a good atmosphere.
Great food service and atmosphere.
My whole family loves the Greek spot. Clean. Good food and they are always nice & friendly. We need more places like this locally!

As a fellow Greek who visits every year, this is THE BEST GYRO i have EVER had in the USA. The pork is just like how they do in Greece, off the skewer. It was my friends first time eating a gyro, she is coming back and was amazed. Even the lamb/beef was said to be the best they have had. Even the fries were seasoned like Greece!!!  ευχαριστώ τους συναδέλφους μου Έλληνες φίλους!!!
Amazing place !!!
great food and very friendly staff.

Take this from a Greek who has had the real thing many times. This was the BEST Gyro I have had in a long time!  Never have I found a spot that had authentic pork Gyros and even put french fries inside!  I highly recommend stopping in for a true Greek meal and experience. It was delicious and a super friendly atmosphere.
Excellent!!  Everything is fresh and delicious!!  Definitely worth the visit, and I will certainly be back!!
Great food great service. Been looking for a a good gyros we are from Chicago and this is as good as back home. Will be back.

The BEST Greek food we've ever had! The Gyros are insanely awesome! And so is everything else! I remember when we had to wait until Oktoberfest every year just to get a taste of these! So glad you opened up a permanent location! Paul and Tina are super friendly and amazing cooks! We have quickly become regulars! Keep up the excellent work guys!!!
Excellent authentic Greek food with outstanding service. A family run restaurant, and you can see the heart and soul put into it. We will definitely be making frequent stops here.

WOW!!! This place is amazing. The food is delicious, the portions are large, and the price is right. You can't go wrong here. The owner's daughter, Glorianna(sp?), is as sweet as the BEST baklava I've ever had! My hubby and I will definitely be repeat customers here😍
Best Gyros in SWFL , we Love this Place , the owners are wonderful!
Wow. Done right. Best food Iv had in awhile. Worthy of my first online review.
Really fresh and bold flavors. Definitely will be back. Great staff.

Great food, fast service and nice Greek music Paul the owner stopped by our table and genuinely concerned that everything was good. We told him It was fantastic, great, awesome and well above our expectations. The only reason he got five stars because we could not give him more stars but it worth ten stars.
Tried for lunch today, both the Greek Spot gyro and side salad were excellent, highly recommend!
Best Greek food in Florida, hands down, thanks for the great meal, and great service, will 100% be back
Great gyros! Definitely needed in the cape.

This little gem has the best gyro in the area. We went for lunch/dinner.  This place is delicious.  My husband and I both had a gyros, mom had the cheese steak.  We split the greek spot fries and they were scrumptious.  The sauce that is served with cheese steak and greek spot fries is spot on.  We ordered the baklava cheesecake and split it, yummy.  We have discovered the best gyro we have ever had in this area.  The bread is soft and fresh, they pita melted in our mouth, yet held together to the last bite of gyro.  The owners are very attentive and this is our new go to for gyros.
This little gem has the best gyro in the area.
A cozy little Gem nestled in the heart of Cape Coral that serves AUTHENTIC GREEK! The owners are absolutely adorable!  Great portion sizes! Great prices! GREAT FOOD!
Finally a Great Greek Restaurant!  Awesome Gyros and Salads, well pretty much everything. Great people, fun place!  Cheers
Pauley is the maestro of the gyro!  Loved it!

Best gyros in town, hands down!! I've been to Crete many times in my Naval career,  and I having been dying to find an authentic Greek gyro. I've been to many Greek restaurants in town and nothing comes close to that authentic taste of Greece. I ordered two gyros, the pork and the beef/lamb gyros. Both were delicious,  brought me back to Greece. The fries were cooked perfect and seasoned well. They gave me a sauce to try, which I think might be a little addicting, it was AMAZING!!!! This will definitely be my new favorite spot in town.
Best Greek food in town HANDS DOWN!! Not too mention so affordable and such large portions! If you haven’t tried your missing out
The BEST Gyro in 10 years!!! Absolutely MY FAVORITE RESTAURANT FOR SERVICE EVER!!
From the minute I walked through the door I was greeted with a smile and had an amazing conversation with everyone inside.  Food is 5/5 Attitude is 5/5 Atmosphere is 5/5
Yummy food and awesome people!!

Guys....GO HERE!!!! The food is amazing. The staff is amazing.  This was our 1st time here. They gyros are huge, my daughter had a Greek salad with chicken that she is able to have for 2 days and the Greek Spot fries....🤤🤤🤤🤤 Ypu guys definitely have new customers!!!!

We just ordered lunch here for the office, and it was so amazing! You definitely will not leave hungry. Everything tasted so fresh, and while it seems like such a small thing - the tomatoes! Oh my gosh, the tomatoes were perfectly ripe. The people are incredibly personable, the service, excellent. We will definitely be using this as one of our go-to lunch spots!

This is definitely the best new restaurant in Cape Coral. We tried the falafel gyros , and they are the best we have ever had. Authentic , filled and the falafel was delicious and not dry at all. We also got Philly cheese steaks and they are better than real Philly ones, as we are from NY and have had Philly ones. The Greek fries are also ridiculous popping with flavor, and the sauce to dip them in is amazing.   We also got a Greek salad just to try it and it was big, flavorful and fresh. A meal in itself.   We will definitely be going back, our new favorite spot.
So excited to have a new greek place in Cape Coral. Portions were huge and food was delicious and amazing! Can't wait to come back again! 😊😁❤
Amazing food and family run!
Amazing food- fresh and good serving sizes.  The falafel and traditional gyro were both delicious.  Baklava and yogurt with honey for dessert.  We will be back for sure!!

The wife & I had traditional Yee-Ros they were so delicious plus had the Greek Spot Fries they were also delicious.  You won’t go away hungry either the portions are big enough to fill you up.  Glad we have a Greek eatery in the Cape and the wife & I will definitely support this family owned and ran restaurant.
Great food and customer service! Will definitely come back!

Opa! There should be a love instead of like button for this family owned much needed Greek Eatery. We were there today on their 1st day and owners Paul, Tina and Nick were welcoming and  so friendly. We quickly settled on flamed at your table saganaki, a traditional gyro and a Greek Salad. Everything was scrumptious. Their house made tzaziki is outstanding. The owners and staff are seasoned professionals. They checked on us and chatted about our experience. Go hungry, the portions are for big appetites! They even gave us a piece of their homemade baklava to take home. Go today for lunch or dinner! You'll love it!
Great food! Fast and very friendly! If you are in the Cape Coral area you must give this place a try! Amazing
Great fresh food and service!
Best Greek food in Florida!
